[Patient] What foods should I eat to help manage my heart failure?
[Educator] Focus on fruits, vegetables, whole grains, lean proteins, and limit sodium, fats, and sugars.
[Patient] Can I still enjoy my favorite traditional dishes?
[Educator] Yes, we can find ways to make them heart-healthy while still keeping their flavors.
[Patient] How can I make sure I am getting enough nutrients?
[Educator] Include a variety of colorful fruits and vegetables in your meals for essential nutrients.
[Patient] What about snacks? Can I still have them?
[Educator] Opt for heart-healthy snacks like nuts, seeds, yogurt, or fruits to satisfy cravings.